WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Welcome to the vocabulary lesson for "Day of the Dead".

2
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Let's start with the word "Cemetery". A cemetery is a place for dead people.

3
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.000
You might also call it a graveyard. So, a cemetery.

4
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Next, we have the word "Ancestors". 

5
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:26.000
Ancestors are the people in your family who lived before you.

6
00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Your grandparents, your great-grandparents, they are your ancestors.

7
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:38.000
Then we have "Somber". Somber means very serious, or sad.

8
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:44.000
In America, cemeteries are usually somber. They are not fun places.

9
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Another word is "Approach". To approach means to come near or closer to something.

10
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:56.000
If you approach a house, you are walking towards the house.

11
00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:02.000
"Passed away" is next. Passed away is a polite way to say died.

12
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:08.000
Instead of saying "he died", you can say "he passed away".

13
00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Okay, those are a few key words for the Day of the Dead story.

14
00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Please listen to this lesson again until you know all the vocabulary perfectly!
